The action icons displayed at the top of the mapping area allow to perform global actions on the Mapper.

**Icon**

**Action**

**Description**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

[**Auto connect**](/doxee-platform/docs/3-dt3-mapper-global-actions#enabling-the-autoconnect-option)

Automatically connect the child nodes of a node with matching names.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

[**Settings**](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-mapper-global-actions#configuring-the-mappers-general-settings)

Define the general settings of the Catalog resource.

## Enabling the auto-connect option
The **Auto connect **option allows to automatically connect all child elements and attributes of an element.

> Note

This option is only available if the input and output structures are the same.

By enabling this option, when you connect a node of the input schema to the corresponding node of the output schema the system automatically connects all the child nodes having the same name.

> Note

For more information on connecting elements, see: [DT3 Mapper - Designing Data Transformations in the Mapping Area.](/doxee-platform/docs/2-dt3-mapper-designing-data-transformations-in-the-mapping-area)

## Configuring the Mapper's general settings
- Open the Mapper resource in the configuration editor as described in [Configuring DT3 Project Resources](/doxee-platform/docs/configuring-dt3-project-resources)

- â€‹Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Settings**). The **Settings **panel is displayed on the right; for example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- Configure the required parameters:

**Section**

**Parameter**

**Description**

**General**

**Name**

Name of the Mapper

**Description**

*(optional) *Brief description of the Mapper

**Action options**

**Use legacy engine**

Select this option to enable the legacy Data Transformation engine.

> Note

For backward compatibility, Data Transformation contains both versions of the Data Mapper processing engine:

Legacy engine (formerly called "Mangler")

- New engine (called "Mapper")

The two engines are functionally equivalent, meaning that applying the same same configuration on the same data will produce the same exact result. The new mapper, though, is faster.

**Schema**

**Manage schemas**

Click on this link to manage the available data schema, as described in [Managing data schemas](/doxee-platform/docs/3-dt3-mapper-global-actions#managing-data-schemas) below.

**Grid manage ment**

**Automatically hide empty columns**

Select this option to automatically hide any empty columns between the configured operators in order to compact the view.

**Automatically hide empty rows**

Select this option to automatically hide any empty rows between the configured operators in order to compact the view.

**Notes manage ment**

**Select page**

Switch to a different page of the Mapper workspace. The available notes (if any) will be displayed at the bottom.

### Managing data schemas
- Click on the **Manage schemas **link to open the dedicated panel; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Move your mouse over the name of a data schema to display the context actions; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select one of the available actions:

**Icon**

**Action**

**Description**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Download**

Download the data schema to your local filesystem.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Rename**

Edit the name of the data schema.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Delete**

Permanently remove the data schema from the project.

> Warning

This action cannot be undone.

If a data schema is currently used by one or more project components, this action is not available.

- If a data schema is used by one or more project components, a blue dot is displayed next to it. Click on it to see which resources are using the structure; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

A detail panel listing the resources already using the selected structure is displayed; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Tip

Click on the name of a resource to open it in its dedicated editor.

It is also possible to download or rename the data schema from this panel.
